Mobiles.ShortDescription: The skeleton of a dwarven miner
Mobiles.LongDescription: `gThe animated skeleton of a dwarf is hacking away at a wall.``
Mobiles.Description: `aThis lich's bones barely hold together after a long time of laborousmining.  It carries a worn pick axe and a leather purse to carry any findsin.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `gA skeletal soldier with spider-webs draped over its skull looks as bored as only a skeleton can.``
Mobiles.Description: `aCobwebs are draped from this lich's skull and shoulders, almost likehair.  What is left of this lich soldier's chainmail and weapons are specksof rust on the dirt-ridden bones.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `gA skeleton carrying a drill trudges through the snow here.``
Mobiles.Description: `aCompletely lacking the motivation it had long ago, when it was made outof more flesh than bone, this skeleton walks from wall to wall, drillingholes at random.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `gOnce a dwarf, now a lich, still a guard, this skeleton protects the castle from intruders.``
Mobiles.Description: `aThe stocky skeleton of a dwarf stands guard here, never departing fromits duty, even in death.  The hollows where eyes once peered out in searchfor malicious elves are always turned to the east, awaiting the enemy.  ``

Mobiles.ShortDescription: The splintered old bones of a skeleton
Mobiles.LongDescription: `gThe splintered old bones of a skeleton try to push a cart full of green ore here.``
Mobiles.Description: `aIn his stubborn tries to move the stuck trolley, this lich has worn hisbones down to splintered stumps.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `gTraktal, the forgotten, has risen from his stony tomb.``
Mobiles.Description: `aApparently the foul magic that turned all dwarves in Bar-Baz into theundead did not even leave the buried alone.  Traktal has risen from the deadand he is in a foul mood.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `fChaos energies have sustained this ancient dwarf, at the same time destroying his mind.``
Mobiles.Description: `fPurple currents worm their way across this dwarves wrinkled skin,apparently originating from his nostrils.  He is clearly insane, but as withany chaos jester, insanity does not necessarily mean "less dangerous".  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `gA white-headed fish swims about here, snapping at anything that moves.``
Mobiles.Description: `aThis black fish would barely be visible in the swirling waters if itwasn't for its white head which earned it its name.  Translucent teethglitters in its maw, completing the illusion of a skull.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `cA worler lurks at the bottom of the maelstrom, creating whirls in the water with its tail.``
Mobiles.Description: `aThis aquatic monster resembles an octopus with its tentacled arms andbeak-like mouth.  It preys on whatever or whoever gets drawn down here bythe great maelstrom.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `gTarn's white bones glow crimson in the light of the furnace.``
Mobiles.Description: `aTarn was once one of the most acclaimed blacksmiths in the world, butnow he is but a shadow of his former self, and his former skill.  Somethingtook his mortality and left him a lich.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `kThe horrible`b furnace monster`k is here, waiting for you!``
Mobiles.Description: `bWhy would anyone let this terrible monster live in their furnace?Sure, it keeps the furnace-stealing thieves away, but feeding it living,screaming flesh, especially if it is your own, seems tiresome.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `gA lich guard patrols the halls of the castle.``
Mobiles.Description: `aThe hollow sound of bone hitting stone resounds in the corridors asthis castle guard patrols, protecting its king.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `gA lich guard patrols the halls of the castle.``
Mobiles.Description: `aThe hollow sound of bone hitting stone resounds in the corridors asthis castle guard patrols, protecting its king.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `gThis female is carefully examining a vein of gold, tapping it with her staff.``
Mobiles.Description: `cClad in the traditional field garb of the amazons, this woman exploresthe surroundings, well aware of your presence, but paying you little heed.You notice that something is hidden under her leaf-colored mantle.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: A bloated red lizard sits here, waiting for its inevitable doom.
Mobiles.Description: `cLike a deer caught in the torch-light, this lizard stares up at you andyour big, big weapon.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `gA lich trudges through the salty waters in search of precious metals.``
Mobiles.Description: `aThe salty waters that would freeze the flesh off the bones off a humanseems to have little effect on this lich.  Its bony fingers fumbles alongthe bottom of the moat in an eternal search for gold.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `gThe lich king radiates a sickly yellow glow that surely will corrupt everything in its proximity.``
Mobiles.Description: `aA traditional dwarven crown made of iron rattles around on the lichking's skull.  Just enough silk falls down his body to hide the skeletonbelow.  Around his neck a key hangs on a golden chain and on his feet a pairof peculiar winged boots.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `gThe big-boned lich chef stands here with a butcher knife in one hand and a decapitated head in the other.``
Mobiles.Description: `aIt was true, what he kept saying about being big-boned, after all!``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `gA lich jailer is here, sleeping on his post.``
Mobiles.Description: `bApparently liches can sleep, if bored enough.  The hard part isdetecting a sleeping lich since they lack eye-lids.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `gClad in rags, this dwarf sits here. Wounds from torture are apparent on his skin.``
Mobiles.Description: `aThis dwarf's body tell a story of torture and starvation.  Dwarves arehardy, but a lengthy incarceration can take its toll even on them.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `gA starved dwarf sits here, scratching his arms frantically.``
Mobiles.Description: `aBleeding sores cover this dwarf's skin, skin that seems to be coveringlittle more than sinew and bone.  Muscles and fat seems to have been eatenup by the prisoner's own body to stay alive.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `gA well-fed and innocent-looking prisoner sits here, smiling broadly.``
Mobiles.Description: `aHappier than one would expect of a prisoner, this dwarf stands herewith an innocent smile on his face.  He mutters "I like it in here, yes sir!Yes, sir!"  And secretly looks toward a loose stone in the floor.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: BLEH!
`gThis warrior sits here dragging a stone along the edge of his axe.``
Mobiles.Description: `aPieces of armor and chainmail hang loose from this skeleton's bones, ahelm rattles on its skull and a great axe grasped in its claw-like fingers.``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `gA lich warrior wanders around the courtyard.``
Mobiles.Description: `aPieces of armor and chainmail hang loose from this skeleton's bones, ahelm rattles on its skull and a great axe grasped in its claw-like fingers.``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `gA defender of the wall keeps both sockets pointed to the east, overlooking the cavern.``
Mobiles.Description: `aPieces of armor and chainmail hang loose from this skeleton's bones, ahelm rattles on its skull and a great axe grasped in its claw-like fingers.``

Mobiles.ShortDescription: The skeleton of a dwarven miner
Mobiles.LongDescription: `gThe animated skeleton of a dwarf is hacking away at a wall.``
Mobiles.Description: `aThis lich's bones barely hold together after a long time of laborousmining.  It carries a worn pick axe and a leather purse to carry any findsin.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `gThe lich king's bodyguard stands here, skeletal arms crossed.``
Mobiles.Description: `aThe eternal loyalty to his king in combination with great fightingskills qualified this lich for a place in the king's bodyguard.  His bonesare chipped and worn from battle but the magic sustaining his undeath stillburns brightly in his eyes.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `gA lich lord stands here, admiring himself in a gold-frame mirror.``
Mobiles.Description: `aClad in expensive silks this lich lord prances around his chambers,throwing an eye-socket in every mirror he passes.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `gThe guard of the treasury stands here, cracking its knuckles.``
Mobiles.Description: `aThis lich's bones are contorted and twisted but does not seem to impedethe warrior's movements at all.  It smiles a toothless grin as it noticesthe intruder.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `gBrobdingnagian, the guard of the treasury stands here, head bowing under the ceiling.``
Mobiles.Description: `aA giant of a skeleton takes up the better part of the room.  He is theguard of the treasury and will make sure nobody enters here alive.  Trapshang from his belt and a a great lance is wielded in his bony fist.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `fA pair of legs hop around here in a peculiar dance. They are actually quite good.``
Mobiles.Description: `hThese dismembered legs hop around in a mesmerizing dance, seeminglyunaware of their lack of body and rhythm.  What helps the overallperformance is the nice-looking dancing shoe one of the feet is wearing.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `iThis room is crawling with spiders! Stomp! Kill!``
Mobiles.Description: `a'`kMommy! Moooommmmmyy!`a'``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `jKing Athanmere slides around on this patch of ice. When will he leave you alone!?``
Mobiles.Description: `fHere he is, again.  King Athanmere is very stern about getting thepeople of the realms to pay tax.  Dressing in his royal garb he travels thelands, looking for you, only you, trying to get you to give him your money.``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `cA singing bush sits on the middle of the ledge, singing. It completely ignores you.``
Mobiles.Description: `a"`kShe'll be coming round the mountain when she comes.`a"```a"`kShe'll be coming round the mountain when she comes.`a"```a"`kShe'll be coming round the mountain,`a"```a"`kShe'll be coming round the mountain,`a" ```a"`kShe'll be coming round the mountain when she comes.`a"`````a"`kOoh...`a"```a"`kShe'll be driving six white horses when she comes...`a"``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `f(Mauve Aura)`a A cat-less tail slithes around here, looking for something. What could it be looking for?``
Mobiles.Description: `hNot much to see here, just a furry tail of a cat that slithers aroundon the ground.  It slithers with a purpose though, it is looking for itslost cat.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `hThe fearsome skeleton of a squirrel stomps about here, scaring you terribly.``
Mobiles.Description: `aFeared throughout Linden and Silver Crescent Woods, Harry, the undeadsquirrel has travelled far and wide to spread fear, mutilate the living andsearch for nuts.  Once of pet of Carnifex himself, this squirrel has therespect of the undead community.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `gA serrated`n battle axe`g with legs walks around here, only wanting a hug.``
Mobiles.Description: `aA chaos jester must have left this poor, abandoned battle axe here forsomeone to find.  Instead of the traditional spider-legs, this vivified axehas two, muscled, human legs.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `gA lookout is here, keeping an eye socket on the happenings in the caverns below.``
Mobiles.Description: `aThis lone skeleton keeps its eye sockets peeled, never letting themisty landscape of the caverns below out of sight.  It reports any intrudersto the defenders on the wall.  ``

Rooms.RoomDescription: `bThis crack in the surface of the world seems to be leading down intosome kind of mining tunnels, and as with most mining tunnels in the realm,these have probably been dug by dwarves.  You feel a chill emanating frombelow, a cold that is more than just the moist low temperature that iscommon to mines.  ``

`bThe low and narrow tunnels and the occasional rune carved into a woodenbeam confirms that these mining tunnels are indeed dwarven.  Nobody has beenmining here for a very long time though, dust is thick beneath and tools arelying around in a disarray that a dwarf would never leave them in.  ``
`bA ramp of rocks, stones and rubble marks the spot of a cave-in.  Thetunnel stops here and no dwarf has been here to restore the tunnel to whatit was.  ``
`bThe tunnel ends in a wall to the west, but in the middle of the waythere is a large hole from which a cold mist oozes out of.  Tendrils of icecreep up from it, ending in puddles of water.  ``

Rooms.ExitMsg: `h$n plods through the snow to to the $T.``
Rooms.RoomDescription: `hA great arc frames the cavern landscape to the west, this seems to bethe gate that marks the entrance to some kind of dwarven undergrounddwelling.  Strangely enough there is snow on the ground.  ``

Rooms.ExitMsg: `h$n plods through the snow to to the $T.``
Rooms.RoomDescription: `hThese are the underground caverns of Bar-Baz, cold mist makes thesnow-covered stone underneath create the illusion of walking on a cloud.Gems glint high above in the roof of the cave and flashes of yellow gleam inyour peripheral vision.``

Rooms.ExitMsg: `h$n stumbles across a pile of snow as $e leaves.``

Rooms.RoomDescription: `hAn ancient crypt made out of white marble rests here between twostalagmites, whatever dwarven runes that proclaimed the name of the dwarfburied here are long gone.  ``

`eStreaming water pulls you down deeper into the murky waters!``

`bStagnant air whirls as the door is opened and the smell of rotting woodwafts by you.  From the hooks and rings that hang from the walls and ceilingone can conclude that this is some kind of storage room.  ``

`hThe material of the drawbridge feels and sounds like both stone andwood, you cannot decide which.  It stretches over the dark moat, and leadsthrough the opening in the outer castle wall.  ``
`bThe courtyard is free of snow, but the frosty mist flows over the wallsfrom the eas.  The dry smell of undeath permeates the grounds, telling youwant you already knew: this is a den of evil.``
`dDwarven runes of warning zig-zag across the floorstones here, goingfarther into the crypt could very well be hazardous to one's health.  A darkpassage continues to the west.  ``
`dDwarven runes of warning zig-zag across the floorstones here, goingfarther into the crypt could very well be hazardous to one's health.  Agreat door is between you and the crypt's main chamber.  ``

`dThis is the main chamber of the crypt, and by the looks of things,whoever was buried here was not buried deep enough.  The lid of the coffinlies broken on the floor and the coffin itself is empty.  ``

`bPurple lightning stream across the surface of the bubble of air,somehow chaos energies suspend the laws of nature here.  To the west thewater whirls in a powerful downward spiral.  ``

`eThis is the source of the maelstrom, the very bottom of the water massspiraling into the depths.  Skulls and bones swirl around in a macabre danceas the current tugs the water in every direction.  ``

`bThree thick stone walls surround you but to the east there is anopening leading out on the wall of the castle.  The stairs continue upwardsto the top of the watchtower.  ``

A great anvildominates the room and close to it are tubs of oil and water.  Heat radiatesfrom the south.  ``

`bThe barracks building is a bit more comfortable than being outside, inthe cold, but years, perhaps decades of use have reduced the furnishings tomear shadows of what they used to be.  Groves can be seen in the stone floorwhere dwarven, later lichen, boots have walked.  ``

`bTo a dwarf, water may be a necessity, but to a lich drinking usuallyinvolved blood, preferably to celebrate killing one of the mortal races.  ``

`bA great gate made of granite inlaid with mithril is apparently aseamless part of the rest of the castle wall.  If any invading army evershould get past the moat and the outer walls, this is where it would stop,despair, and turn back.  ``

`bThe heat in here is enourmous, great open furnaces roar with fire andin them pieces of steel are kept molten white.  A wooden crate filled withcoal sits on the far west side, at he opposite side of the furnaces.  ``

`bOn top of the lich king's, once the dwarf chieftan's, castle walls, youoverlook the great cavern to the east.  Through the freezing mists you seethe glimmer of snow and the shadows that are the lumbering lich creatures.``

`bNarrow, dwarf-sized corridors lead into the castle of Bar-Baz.Flickering torches light the way but offer no comfort, after all, whatcomfort is light and warmth in a keep full of undead warriors?  ``

`bEven though the walls are marble and expensive tapestries and beautifulred mats adorn the corridors of this castle, the fact that it was carved outof the side of a gargantuan cave is somehow apparent.``

`bEven though the walls are marble and expensive tapestries and beautifulred mats adorn the corridors of this castle, the fact that it was carved outof the side of a gargantuan cave is somehow apparent.``
`bFlower-patterned silks and tapestries adorn the walls here, between theplentiful amount of mirrors.  Back west is the northern corridor.  ``

`bA narrow staircase leads down into the dungeon where the stench,screams and mad laughter of prisoners await.  The reinforced door to thewest looks much less inpenetrable on this side of the door.  ``

`bSteel doors line the dungeon walls.  This is where the enemies of thelich king gets to sit and do nothing for the rest of their lives.Occasional screams can be heard as some prisoner decides the silence is toomuch to take``
`bFour walls, a ceiling and a floor, all made of stone.  This cell smellslike somebody died in it, which is not a very far-fetched thought.  ``

Rooms.RoomDescription: `bThe heart of the dwarf castle: the treasury.  This is where all theking's riches are locked in.  Protected by guards, traps and foot-thickstone doors.  ``
`bThe heart of the dwarf castle: the treasury.  This is where all theking's riches are locked in.  Protected by guards, traps and foot-thickstone doors.  ``

`bA marble stair leads up to the dwarf-sized throne and torches spreadtheir light all the way up.  To the east the hollow thumping of the lichguards' feet are heard as they patrol along the corridors.  ``
`bThough beautiful, in the rugged dwarf way, there is something wrongwith this room.  It is as if the mere presence of the lich king makes theair foul and the very stone rot.  ``

`bEven though the walls are marble and expensive tapestries and beautifulred mats adorn the corridors of this castle, the fact that it was carved outof the side of a gargantuan cave is somehow apparent.``

`bThe strongroom is strangely empty.  The piles of silver and gold areabsent and no jewels lie strewn on the stone floor.  A vein of quartz leadin light from the surface and casts its light on a lone steel chest.  ``

`hHigh above the floor of the cavern is this ledge.  This is a placewhere mystical chaos energies leak from another world, transforming itssurroundings to a warped reality.  A singing bush does what it does bestwhile waving its branches around.  ``
`bTreacherous stairs spiral up inside the tower like intestines of astone giant.  The torches that light the way are few and far between, and tomake bad worse: they are all unlit.  ``

`bFrom up here most of the cavern is visible below and a looking-glassstands aimed at the farawar gate on its tripod.  To the south you can seethe wall where defenders handles the catapult and keeps a lookout.  ``
